properties.areaDesc: East Entrance U.S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 14 at 2:58PM PST until January 16 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, southeast winds 20 to 30
kt. For the Gale Watch, southeast winds 30 to 40 kt possible.

* WHERE...East Entrance U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 4 AM to 4 PM PST
Wednesday. For the Gale Watch, from Wednesday afternoon
through Thursday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased, but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.
